'''危機處置''' ([[:en:crisis_intervention|crisis intervention]])不是長期性的介入方式，而是有時限性(time-limited)的，其主要在協助個人或團體安然渡過混亂事件的助人過程，使其能夠縮小負面的影響程度。除了幫助個案回復到危機發生前的功能狀況，並加大成長的可能性<ref>{{cite book |last= Thompson |first= Rosemary A. |title= '' Crisis Intervention and Crisis Management '' |publisher= Brunner-Routledge |year= 2004 |isbn= 0-415-94494-5 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last= Conner |first= Michael G. |title= '' Crisis Intervention with Adolescents: A Parent Guide'' |publisher= AuthorHouse |year= 2005 |isbn= 1-4208-9235-5 }}</ref><ref name="multiple" />。此处的“危机”(古希臘語：krisis)意謂身處在一個決定性的緊要關頭或轉折點，而危機的英文([[:en:crisis|crisis]])意涵同時是危險(Danger)與機會(Opportunity)([[:en:chinese_word_for_"crisis"|chinese word for "crisis"]])。具體來說，危機是「個人在面對一個既無法逃脫，且利用現有的問題解決資源又無法解決危急事件時所經驗的一段短暫心理不平衡(disequilibrium)時期」<ref name="multiple">{{cite conference |author=陳嘉鳳 |coauthors= 周才忠、賴念華、錢靜怡與利美萱 |title=[http://compsy.idv.tw/papers/ci001.pdf 危機處置之理論與實務：以第一現場相關處置為例] |booktitle= 社區諮商學術與實務研討會論文集|pages=23-52 |year=2005 |publisher=國立高雄師範大學}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite book |last= Echterling |first= Lennis G. |coauthors= Jack H. Presbury, J. Edson McKee |title= '' Crisis Intervention: Promoting Resilience and Resolution in Troubled Times '' |publisher= Pearson Education |year= 2005 |isbn= 0-13-090897-5 }}</ref><ref name="ref1">{{cite book |last= James |first= Richard K. |coauthors= Burl E. Gilliland |title= '' Crisis Intervention Strategies '' |url= https://archive.org/details/crisisinterventi0000jame |publisher= Wadsworth/Thomson |year= 2004 |isbn= 0-534-56966-8 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last= Kanel |first= Kristi |title= '' A Guide to Crisis Intervention '' |url= https://archive.org/details/guidetocrisisint0000kane |publisher= Brooks/Cole |year= 2003 |isbn= 0-53454-794-X }}</ref>。

